azon</a></div></div></div></div><h2 data-node-id="18" class="body-h2 css-16fdti9 emevuu60"><strong data-redactor-tag="strong" data-node-id="18.0">5. Always keep a nail file on hand.</strong></h2><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="19" class="body-text css-i9p093 emevuu60">If your job or workout routine exposes your nails to potential damage, Dr. Prystowsky advises keeping a nail file handy for on-the-spot buffing of any rough edges. For the smoothest finish, work in one direction with the grain of your nail. </p><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="20" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">Instead of an emory board, which can cause nails to peel and snag, try a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01N9B27XA?linkCode=ogi&amp;tag=goodhousekeeping_auto-append-20&amp;ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C10055.a.34645%5Bsrc%7Clocalhost%5Bch%7C%5Blt%7C%5Bpid%7C81810577-8f13-44d8-a7be-82afdda4b8f6%5Baxid%7C52841d0c-886a-4a7d-9a6c-7691b336a200" rel="nofollow noskim" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01N9B27XA" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="glass (also called crystal) nail file" data-vars-ga-product-id="81810577-8f13-44d8-a7be-82afdda4b8f6" data-node-id="20.1" data-href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01N9B27XA" data-product-url="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01N9B27XA" data-affiliate="true" data-affiliate-url="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01N9B27XA?tag=goodhousekeeping_auto-append-20" data-affiliate-network="{&quot;afflink_redirect&quot;:&quot;/_p/afflink/bIRT/amazon-glass-nail-file-mont&quot;,&quot;site_id&quot;:&quot;8342522f-11a7-4c85-8c15-51f36ee1d53f&quot;,&quot;network&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Amazon&quot;},&quot;metadata&quot;:{&quot;links&quot;:{&quot;default&quot;:&quot;https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01N9B27XA?tag=goodhousekeeping_auto-append-20&quot;,&quot;sem&quot;:&quot;https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01N9B27XA?tag=ghk-lift-20&quot;,&quot;social&quot;:&quot;https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01N9B27XA?tag=ghk-soc-lift-20&quot;}}}" data-vars-ga-product-brand="Mont Bleu" data-vars-ga-product-price="$9.95" data-vars-ga-product-retailer-id="b2e043fd-0a54-41da-bd8d-86c7c5bc9f49" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-brand="Mont Bleu" data-vars-ga-product-sem3-category="Nail Files &amp; Buffers" data-vars-ga-link-treatment="(not set) | (not set)" class="body-link product-links css-h40fkh e1aq0z090" data-vars-ga-axid="52841d0c-886a-4a7d-9a6c-7691b336a200" data-amazon-ascsubtag="[artid|10055.a.34645[src|localhost[ch|[lt|[pid|81810577-8f13-44d8-a7be-82afdda4b8f6[axid|52841d0c-886a-4a7d-9a6c-7691b336a200" data-aps-asc-tag="goodhousekeeping_auto-append-20" data-aps-asc-subtag="[artid|10055.a.34645[src|localhost[ch|[lt|[pid|81810577-8f13-44d8-a7be-82afdda4b8f6[axid|52841d0c-886a-4a7d-9a6c-7691b336a200">glass (also called crystal) nail file</a>. "A glass file will create an even edge to the nail and can be used on the weakest, brittle, and damaged nails," Dr. Stern says.</p><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-1-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" data-journey-unblur="true" class="breaker-ad css-losvwb e1spmc111"><div data-journey-unblur="true" class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-172ho3e e1spmc110"><div class="ad-disclaimer no-print css-q3d0ua e1caqep90">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div data-slot-type="breaker" id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-1" suppresshydrationwarning="true" class="ad-container css-11u1es3 ewg5wdb1"><div id="gpt_lb_1" class="gpt-adslot noskim"></div></div></div></section><h2 data-node-id="21" class="body-h2 css-16fdti9 emevuu60"><strong data-node-id="21.0">6. Don't forget to take care of your nail tools, too.</strong></h2><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="22" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">Disinfecting your nail tools between uses is just as important as regularly <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/makeup/g2822/how-to-clean-makeup-brushes/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/makeu