a6c" data-amazon-ascsubtag="[artid|10055.a.34645[src|localhost[ch|[lt|[pid|02cd5f76-066a-45ad-912b-f30fcb59fd84[axid|451574af-f26e-42ee-8e4f-eb1da77daa6c" data-aps-asin="B0016K8B54" data-aps-asc-tag="goodhousekeeping_auto-append-20" data-aps-asc-subtag="[artid|10055.a.34645[src|localhost[ch|[lt|[pid|02cd5f76-066a-45ad-912b-f30fcb59fd84[axid|451574af-f26e-42ee-8e4f-eb1da77daa6c">$6 at Amazon</a></div></div></div></div><h2 data-node-id="32" class="body-h2 css-16fdti9 emevuu60"><strong data-redactor-tag="strong" data-node-id="32.0">10. Use a top coat to prevent nail chips.</strong></h2><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="33" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">Don't think you can skip a <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/product-reviews/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/product-reviews/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="top coat" data-node-id="33.1" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">top coat</a>, either. This step is just as important, as the top coat seals in the polish's color and adds a much-needed gloss finish to your digits. Dr. Prystowsky recommends adding another top coat layer every three days to decrease chipping, so you'll get the most out of your manicure. </p><section id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-2-wrapper" data-type="breaker-ad" data-journey-unblur="true" class="breaker-ad css-losvwb e1spmc111"><div data-journey-unblur="true" class="gpt-breaker-container breaker-ad clearfix css-172ho3e e1spmc110"><div class="ad-disclaimer no-print css-q3d0ua e1caqep90">Advertisement - Continue Reading Below</div><div data-slot-type="breaker" id="article-ad-breaker-leaderboard-2" suppresshydrationwarning="true" class="ad-container css-11u1es3 ewg5wdb1"><div id="gpt_lb_2" class="gpt-adslot noskim"></div></div></div></section><h2 data-node-id="34" class="body-h2 css-16fdti9 emevuu60"><strong data-redactor-tag="strong" data-node-id="34.0">11. Indulge in acrylic or gel treatments sparingly.</strong></h2><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="35" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">Any nail expert you talk to is going to do their best to steer you away from <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/nails/a47362/how-to-remove-acrylic-nails/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/nails/a47362/how-to-remove-acrylic-nails/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="acrylic or gel manicures" data-node-id="35.1" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">acrylic or gel manicures</a> — as long-lasting and convenient as they are because they're very hard on the nail. But if you're keen on getting them, there are some ways to minimize the damage to your hands and nails. </p><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="36" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">The main issue with a gel manicure is the exposure to UV light in the drying device, which can damage the skin below and around the nail, leading to an increased risk of cancer. To help reduce that risk, Dr. Prystowsky recommends <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/anti-aging/g1288/best-sunscreens/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/anti-aging/g1288/best-sunscreens/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="applying a sunscreen" data-node-id="36.1" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">applying a sunscreen</a> with an SPF of 30 to 50 before the procedure to help block the damage, or you can try special gloves that expose only the nails themselves, shielding the rest of your hands from the harmful UV rays. </p><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="37" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">There's also a professional service that the <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/about/institute/a19748212/good-housekeeping-institute-product-reviews/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/about/institute/a19748212/good-housekeeping-institute-product-reviews/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Good Housekeeping Institute" data-node-id="37.1" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">Good Housekeeping Institute</a>'s Beauty Lab found won't ruin your nails: CND's <a href="https://cnd.com/cnd-shellac-luxe/w" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://cnd.com/cnd-shellac-luxe/w" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Shellac Luxe" data-node-id="37.3" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">Shellac Luxe</a> salon service, which won a <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty-products/a26991563/best-beauty-awards-2019/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty-products/a26991563/best-beauty-awards-2019/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="Good Housekeeping Beauty Award in 2019" data-node-id="37.5" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">Good Housekeeping Beauty Award in 2019</a>. </p><h2 data-node-id="38" class="body-h2 css-16fdti9 emevuu60"><strong data-redactor-tag="strong" data-node-id="38.0">12. Give your nails a break.</strong></h2><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="39" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">Save the <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/nails/g2538/summer-nail-art-ideas/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/nails/g2538/summer-nail-art-ideas/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="elaborate nail art" data-node-id="39.1" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">elaborate nail art</a> and those bold colors with lots of pigment for the weekend, and during the rest of the week, give your nails time to rest and repair with a clear gloss. Dr. Shamban warns that going from one strong polish color to another without giving your nails a break can dry them out, turn them yellow, and over time, even weaken the structure of the nail. </p><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="40" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">Dr. Stern agrees, saying that nail polish removers could also be the reason your nails are weak. Sometimes going all natural "can be just the thing that your nails need in order to rejuvenate and refresh," she says. </p><section data-embed="editorial-link" data-lazy-id="P0-16" data-node-id="41" class="embed"><aside class="css-epuhkm e94w1mj9"><h6 class="css-y4ppz4 e94w1mj7"><span aria-hidden="true" data-theme-key="title-design-element-before" class="css-0 eagam8p0"></span><span class="css-8lle59 e94w1mj5">FROM OUR BEAUTY SCIENTISTS</span><span aria-hidden="true" data-theme-key="title-design-element-after" class="css-0 eagam8p1"></span></h6><ul class="css-c4s2gi e94w1mj8"><li class="css-14t2m3b e94w1mj6"><a data-theme-key="base-link" href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty-products/a25136153/best-hand-cream/" class="css-1bn7a5e e1c1bym14"><span aria-hidden="true" data-theme-key="title-design-element-before" class="css-0 eagam8p0"></span><img src="./15 Tips for Healthy, Strong Nails - The Best Nail Care Tips_files/best-hand-creams-68026ddf244f2.png" alt="" title="The Best Hand Creams to Buy This Year" width="108" height="100%" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="css-1l0uuk1 e94w1mj4"><span class="css-8lle59 e94w1mj5">The Best Hand Creams to Buy This Year</span><span aria-hidden="true" data-theme-key="title-design-element-after" class="css-0 eagam8p1"></span></a></li></ul></aside></section><h2 data-node-id="42" class="body-h2 css-16fdti9 emevuu60">13. Moisturize your hands and nails regularly.</h2><p data-journey-content="true" data-node-id="43" class="css-i9p093 emevuu60">You <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty-products/g5014/best-face-moisturizer/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty-products/g5014/best-face-moisturizer/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="moisturize your face" data-node-id="43.1" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">moisturize your face</a> before bed, so do the same for your nails. New York City nail expert Holly Falcone likes to use a mix of almond and avocado oils to keep cuticles and nails hydrated while she gets some shut-eye, but any nutrient-rich oil or moisturizer will do. In a pinch, you can even use a dab of <a href="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/makeup/g3325/best-lip-balms/" target="_blank" data-vars-ga-outbound-link="https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/beauty/makeup/g3325/best-lip-balms/" data-vars-ga-ux-element="Hyperlink" data-vars-ga-call-to-action="lip balm" data-node-id="43.3" class="body-link css-h40fkh emevuu60">lip balm</a>. "Efficacious formulas contain humectant ingredients like glycerin, emollients such as fatty oils and occlusives like silicones, which work together to hydrate nails and skin," says Wnek.</p><h2 data-node-id="44" class="body-h2 css-16fdti9 emevuu60"><strong data-redactor-tag="strong" data-node-id="44.0">14. Wear gloves when doing dishes.</strong></h2><div data-ad-exclude="(min-width: 90rem)" data-embed="embed-product" data-node-id="45" data-theme-key="embedded-product-wrapper" size="small" class="size-small align-right embed css-nygxqo e1ydkxnk0"><div id="product-bf855bef-04e8-4750-9fe5-524bdbc48f1d" data-anchor-id="product-bf855bef-04e8-4750-9fe5-524bdbc48f1d" class="css-17pp2fn e1ydkxnk1"></div><div size="small" class="size-small align-right css-60ezry ebgq4gw7"><a target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noskim" data-theme-key="product-image-wrapper" href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00SRR8I16?linkCode=ogi&amp;tag=goodhousekeeping_auto-append-20&amp;ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C10055.a.34645%5Bsrc%7Clocalhost%5Bch%7C%5Blt%7Csale%5Bpid%7Cbf855bef-04e8-4750-9fe5-524bdbc48f1d%5Baxid%7C407ad0e6-8e29-48e6-9048-d7ab32fe88f8" aria-label="$15 at Amazon for Playtex Living Reuseable Rubber Cleaning Gloves" data-href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00SRR8I16" data-product-url="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00SRR8I16" data-affiliate="